      • binarySearch

        private int binarySearch(E theValue)
        Binary search algorithm that is O(log(n)), and only relevant on a sorted list in ascending order, and assumes the list is not empty. If the data exists, it shall be found within 7 loop iterations.
        Parameters:
        theValue - the value to search for.
        Returns:
        the index of the data found, else if not found then the same index number is returned, but negated.
